    <label>Photosynthetic Fleshleaf Embryo</label>
    <description>A pale, gelatinous sprout with four budding lobes, faintly translucent and gently twitching in response to light. As it matures, the embryo develops a thin, green-tinged membrane — a sign of its photosynthetic potential. Once fully grown, it will unfurl its fleshy lobes to capture sunlight and generate hemogel for the colony.</description>
